  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Shipping Operation Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job\nSummary</strong></p><p>We are\nlooking for a detail-oriented Vessel Operation Executive to handle daily vessel\noperations and operational documentation for chartered vessels. The role\nsupports the chartering/shipping desk by ensuring smooth voyage execution,\naccurate operational records, and proper handling of laytime, demurrage, and\nclaims in accordance with charter party terms.</p><p><strong>Key\nResponsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Handle day-to-day vessel operations for\n     chartered vessels (voyage/time charter)</li><li>Coordinate with ship owners, operators,\n     agents, brokers, and internal chartering/trading teams</li><li>Monitor vessel schedules, ETA/ETD, port\n     operations, loading/discharging activities</li><li>Ensure vessel operations are performed in\n     compliance with Charter Party terms</li><li>Prepare, check, and maintain operational\n     documents and records, including SOF, NOR, port logs, and voyage files</li><li>Maintain accurate operation records,\n     reports, and filing systems for each voyage</li><li>Prepare operational reports and provide\n     timely updates to management and chartering team</li><li>Support laytime calculation,\n     demurrage/despatch (DEM/DESP) follow-up</li><li>Assist in handling demurrage claims and\n     operational claims, including document collection and coordination with\n     relevant parties</li><li>Follow up and review PDA/FDA and\n     operational costs related to voyages</li><li>Coordinate bunkering, port services, and\n     vessel requirements as needed</li><li>Identify, report, and follow up on\n     operational issues, delays, or deviations during voyages</li><li>Perform other duties related to vessel\n     operations as assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Job\nRequirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 years of experience in vessel\n     operations / chartering operations / shipping operations</li><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Maritime\n     Studies, Shipping, Logistics, or related fields</li><li>Good understanding of Charter Party,\n     vessel operations, and shipping practices</li><li>Familiar with laytime calculation, SOF,\n     demurrage/despatch, and claims handling</li><li>Experience in documentation, reporting,\n     and operational record keeping</li><li>Strong coordination, communication, and\n     organizational skills</li><li>Ability to work independently and handle\n     multiple voyages simultaneously</li><li>Proficient in MS Office</li><li>Good command of English (written and\n     spoken)</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
